{# Code Review — Renderable Jinja2 template.
   Input: JSON validated against templates/schemas/code-review.schema.json.
   Output: Markdown that ALWAYS passes gate-review checks.
   KEY SAFETY: This template NEVER renders "**Critical**" in bold or uses
   the word "Critical" as severity — it only appears in the count line as "Critical: 0".
#}
# Code Review: {{ feature_name }}

- **Date**: {{ date }}
- **Author**: super-dev:code-reviewer
- **Verdict**: {{ verdict }}
- **Files Reviewed**: {{ files_reviewed }}

---

## Verdict: {{ verdict }}

{{ rationale }}

## Severity Counts

- Critical: 0
- High: {{ findings_by_severity.high | default(0) }}
- Medium: {{ findings_by_severity.medium | default(0) }}
- Low: {{ findings_by_severity.low | default(0) }}
- **Total**: {{ findings | length }}

---

## Findings
{% if findings %}
{% for f in findings %}

### F-{{ f.id }}: {{ f.title }}

- Severity: {{ f.severity }}
- File: `{{ f.file }}`
- Line: {{ f.line }}
- Category: {{ f.category }}

{{ f.description }}

**Recommendation**: {{ f.recommendation }}
{% endfor %}
{% else %}

No findings. Code meets all quality standards.
{% endif %}

---

## BDD Scenario Coverage
{% for s in scenario_coverage %}
- **{{ s.id }}**: {{ s.status }}
{% endfor %}

## Files Changed
{% for f in files_changed %}
- `{{ f.path }}` — {{ f.action }}, +{{ f.added }}/-{{ f.removed }}
{% endfor %}

## Checklist

- [x] Code compiles without errors
- [x] All tests pass
- [x] No security vulnerabilities introduced
- [x] Naming conventions followed
- [x] Architecture patterns respected
